Welcome to our ProjectHello everyone and welcome in our project “Beyond All Unreasonable doubt”.My name’s Antonio Candalice and I’m a young Italian director. I have recently created "Candalice Production", an independent production in my city, Bari. This beautiful Italian city is one of the new centres of the film production in Italy. With the team of my independent production we want to transform ideas and projects in cinematographic reality and promote new artists.After high school diploma, I studied for two years Directing and Directing of photography at the Film Academy “Amarcord” in Bari. My teachers were Stefano Reali and Raffaele Mertes, two important Italian directors. During this period in the Academy, I produced two short films, “Soapera” (2019) and “How High The Moon” (2020). My first self-produced short film was “Just A Normal Day” (2019), based on feminine stereotypes, that reached over the 100000 views on the social platform. In 2019 I also co-produced the short film “Ci Scappa Il Morto” for a local film festival, “Tagliacorto”.My first work realized with Candalice Production was “Bureaucardiocracy” (2020), finalist in many Italian and international Film Festival Awards and actually enrolled to the next edition of “David di Donatello”.Actually we're working to this new project, “Beyond All Unreasonable Doubt”, that it’s going to be realized on May 2021 (if Covid gives us his consent).The Project “Beyond All Unreasonable Doubt” is the pilot of a next TV-series or web series. The plot circles around Zoe Olmi, a famous woman criminologist engaged in a new complicated murder happened in Bari. On the road she meets a strange journalist, Margareth Thompson, that reveals her an uncomfortable truth: Lucusta, a serial killer that Zoe thought she captured few years ago, is still free and he’s back in action. All the Zoe’s certainties are put in crisis and they fall down when she does an incredible strike in Bari.Why we need your helpWe are all in a very difficult moment. Also the big cinematographic industry is suffering the effects of pandemic, especially little independent production that generally produce great masterpieces with small budget.We trust public is not only a simple passive receiver of a film, but he can be an active participant of a artistic project if he decides to support it.Your support, then, would allow this pilot to come to life, becoming co-producers. Your support would increase also the chances that this project becomes something bigger.BudgetTo make this project we need €5000, that will be used entirely for the realization of the pilot. This is the list of necessary expenses:
Rent for the space for casting;
Equipment for shooting;
Rent lighting system;
Creation of vfx (special effects);
Payment of artistic and technical cast;
Payment taxes for public areas;
Vehicle rental for the transport of equipments;
Travel expenses;
Security measures to prevent Covid-19;
Catering.
Reaching this goals means allowing Candalice Production to grow artistically and become a point of reference for many Italian and non-Italian talented artists.If you can’t help with monetary contribution, you can support it sharing this campaign on your social account.Thank you very much for your help.
